1
00:00:13,233 --> 00:00:16,067
<i> Felma, I'll go for now.</i>

2
00:00:16,200 --> 00:00:19,000
<i>If you need anything,
just call me, okay?</i>

3
00:00:23,067 --> 00:00:24,600
<i> We're here to make a deal.</i>

4
00:00:24,733 --> 00:00:25,633
<i> What are you going to do?</i>

5
00:00:25,767 --> 00:00:27,467
<i> You're canceling the TRO?</i>

6
00:00:27,600 --> 00:00:30,700
<i>Coleen, why didn't you tell us
before doing that?</i>

7
00:00:30,833 --> 00:00:33,667
<i>It was the only way I could
think of to keep the peace.</i>

8
00:00:33,800 --> 00:00:34,933
<i> What about Mom?</i>

9
00:00:35,100 --> 00:00:36,733
<i>Wasn't she the one who filed
that restraining order?</i>

10
00:00:36,867 --> 00:00:38,500
<i>- Does she know?
- No.</i>

11
00:00:38,633 --> 00:00:41,367
<i> I've got a headache.</i>

12
00:00:41,500 --> 00:00:44,600
<i>I'm just going to the restroom.
Just wait for me.</i>

13
00:00:44,733 --> 00:00:48,633
<i>Wow, that chicken soup
smells really good, sweetie!</i>

14
00:00:48,767 --> 00:00:50,733
<i>I really made it special
for Mom and Dad.</i>

15
00:00:50,867 --> 00:00:53,400
<i>Miss, could you check
if my wife is inside?</i>

16
00:00:53,533 --> 00:00:55,300
<i> She's sick.</i>

17
00:00:55,433 --> 00:00:57,767
<i> They're taking so long.</i>

18
00:00:57,900 --> 00:00:59,600
<i> Felma isn't inside, sir.</i>

19
00:00:59,733 --> 00:01:00,733
<i> Are you sure, miss?</i>

20
00:01:00,867 --> 00:01:02,767
<i>Yes, sir. There were only
two women in there.</i>

21
00:01:02,900 --> 00:01:04,467
<i> Neither of them was Felma.</i>

22
00:01:04,600 --> 00:01:06,067
<i> Did Felma come in here?</i>

23
00:01:06,200 --> 00:01:07,800
<i> Weren't you with Felma?</i>

24
00:01:07,967 --> 00:01:09,033
<i> Where is she?</i>

25
00:01:09,167 --> 00:01:11,233
<i> She's missing.</i>

26
00:01:20,200 --> 00:01:21,233
Felma?

27
00:01:25,600 --> 00:01:26,633
Felma!

28
00:01:29,033 --> 00:01:31,833
We need to see her right away.

29
00:01:31,967 --> 00:01:33,900
She's sick.

30
00:01:34,033 --> 00:01:36,033
It's dangerous
for her to be alone.

31
00:01:36,167 --> 00:01:39,033
Alright, sir.
I'll alert the others.

32
00:01:39,167 --> 00:01:40,467
Thank you so much.

33
00:01:42,233 --> 00:01:43,133
Felma?

34
00:01:44,600 --> 00:01:46,033
Felma!

35
00:01:52,700 --> 00:01:54,033
Miss?

36
00:01:54,167 --> 00:01:57,700
Miss! Have you seen a woman
who looks like this?

37
00:01:57,833 --> 00:02:00,133
Oh, sorry. I haven't.

38
00:02:00,267 --> 00:02:01,400
Thanks.

39
00:02:04,900 --> 00:02:07,467
- Felma?
- Manuel!

40
00:02:07,600 --> 00:02:09,300
Any news from Abel?

41
00:02:10,200 --> 00:02:11,300
Still nothing.

42
00:02:12,300 --> 00:02:15,667
Maybe Felma got confused?

43
00:02:15,833 --> 00:02:18,133
Like what you said happened
the other day.

44
00:02:18,267 --> 00:02:19,967
That's exactly
what I'm afraid of, Manuel.

45
00:02:20,100 --> 00:02:22,467
Sir, about the woman
you're looking for.

46
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:24,567
Here's a copy
of the CCTV footage.

47
00:02:24,700 --> 00:02:27,500
She exited through the
fire exit near the restroom.

48
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:33,167
That's why I didn't see
her leave.

49
00:02:34,200 --> 00:02:35,800
Guard,

50
00:02:35,933 --> 00:02:37,100
do you know where she went?

51
00:02:37,233 --> 00:02:39,800
We're not sure, sir. She may
have already left the airport.

52
00:02:42,400 --> 00:02:43,633
Thank you.

53
00:02:43,767 --> 00:02:45,033
- Thank you.
- Come on.

54
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:02,733
What could've happened?
They're taking forever.

55
00:03:02,867 --> 00:03:04,367
Mom's not answering either.

56
00:03:04,500 --> 00:03:08,000
Uncle Noah isn't replying
to my messages.

57
00:03:08,133 --> 00:03:09,433
What is going on?

58
00:03:09,567 --> 00:03:12,367
It was easier to contact
your Uncle Abel

59
00:03:12,500 --> 00:03:14,900
when he was in Saudi Arabia
than now.

60
00:03:15,033 --> 00:03:18,700
I just hope nothing
bad happened to them.

61
00:03:25,500 --> 00:03:26,867
Bro? Nothing?

62
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:28,600
Nothing.
I've been asking around, too.

63
00:03:28,733 --> 00:03:31,400
Look. Paz has been messaging
me nonstop.

64
00:03:31,533 --> 00:03:33,433
The kids are looking for us.

65
00:03:33,567 --> 00:03:34,833
Manuel,

66
00:03:36,133 --> 00:03:39,600
should we tell the kids
so they can help?

67
00:03:41,233 --> 00:03:42,900
But Felma wanted to be the one

68
00:03:43,033 --> 00:03:46,167
to tell them
about her condition.

69
00:03:46,300 --> 00:03:47,833
I know.

70
00:03:47,967 --> 00:03:50,767
But what matters now
is finding Felma.

71
00:03:58,700 --> 00:04:00,567
Dad, why would Mom do that?

72
00:04:00,700 --> 00:04:01,867
Yeah,

73
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:03,800
Mom knows how worried
we all were

74
00:04:03,933 --> 00:04:05,567
when she left
without telling anyone.

75
00:04:05,700 --> 00:04:08,033
Son, I don't know either.

76
00:04:08,167 --> 00:04:11,867
Let's just work together
to find her as soon as possible.

77
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:14,867
Okay. I'll coordinate
with the police.

78
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:16,933
I'll post online, too.

79
00:04:17,067 --> 00:04:18,267
Dad, stay there, okay?
I'm coming to you.

80
00:04:18,400 --> 00:04:20,000
Mom might not have gone far.

81
00:04:20,133 --> 00:04:21,400
I'll come with you, Jeff.

82
00:04:21,533 --> 00:04:23,100
Wait.

83
00:04:23,233 --> 00:04:25,967
Dad, what if someone
threatened Mom

84
00:04:26,100 --> 00:04:28,533
to make her stay away from you?

85
00:04:39,167 --> 00:04:40,467
Felma!

86
00:04:43,333 --> 00:04:44,900
Just a second!

87
00:04:45,033 --> 00:04:46,367
What's with the doorbell?

88
00:04:46,500 --> 00:04:48,267
Wait! What is it?

89
00:04:48,400 --> 00:04:49,567
Wait!

90
00:04:49,700 --> 00:04:50,833
- What is it?
- Hazel, where's Felma?

91
00:04:50,967 --> 00:04:53,333
- Manuel?
- Where's Felma?

92
00:04:53,467 --> 00:04:55,667
Manuel, what are you going?
Hey! Wait!

93
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:57,067
- Felma!
- Manuel! Hold on!

94
00:04:57,200 --> 00:04:58,333
Felma!

95
00:04:58,467 --> 00:05:00,967
Manuel, she's not here.
What are you talking about?

96
00:05:01,133 --> 00:05:04,667
- She's not here. Manuel!
- Felma!

97
00:05:04,800 --> 00:05:06,033
- What is wrong with you?
- Felma!

98
00:05:06,167 --> 00:05:09,033
I already told you,
she's not here!

99
00:05:09,167 --> 00:05:10,800
- Where is Felma?
- She's not here!

100
00:05:10,933 --> 00:05:12,567
- What are you saying?
- Where's Felma?

101
00:05:12,700 --> 00:05:14,867
She's not here!
She's not here, right?

102
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:16,900
- Yes, she's not here.
- Friend, don't tell me

103
00:05:17,033 --> 00:05:18,167
you've gone as far
as kidnapping now.

104
00:05:18,300 --> 00:05:19,700
What?
What are you talking about?

105
00:05:19,833 --> 00:05:21,667
- She's not here.
- You're lying!

106
00:05:21,800 --> 00:05:23,767
Where is Felma?

107
00:05:23,900 --> 00:05:25,067
Where is she?

108
00:05:25,200 --> 00:05:28,033
Let go of me!

109
00:05:28,167 --> 00:05:30,200
Why are you looking for her
here? Weren't you together?

110
00:05:33,633 --> 00:05:35,733
Maybe she's with Noah.

111
00:05:35,900 --> 00:05:40,200
Maybe she realized
he's more useful than you.

112
00:05:40,333 --> 00:05:41,900
She's not with Noah.

113
00:05:43,267 --> 00:05:45,233
Oh, maybe she went
back to her house.

114
00:05:45,367 --> 00:05:47,467
In hell. She went back there.

115
00:05:48,467 --> 00:05:51,300
Hazel, you're the one
with a house there, not Felma.

116
00:05:51,433 --> 00:05:54,867
Abel, stop stirring things up.

117
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:56,667
- Felma!
- Hey!

118
00:05:56,800 --> 00:05:58,767
- Felma!
- She's not here!

119
00:05:58,900 --> 00:06:01,233
Enough already, Manuel!

120
00:06:01,367 --> 00:06:02,633
What did you expect, huh?

121
00:06:02,767 --> 00:06:05,500
That I kidnapped her
and hid her here?

122
00:06:05,633 --> 00:06:07,067
You're always like this, Manuel.

123
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:09,500
You accuse me without proof!

124
00:06:09,667 --> 00:06:11,667
Who else would I accuse?

125
00:06:11,800 --> 00:06:14,200
You're the only one
who'd hurt Felma!

126
00:06:14,333 --> 00:06:15,500
Did it ever occur to you

127
00:06:15,633 --> 00:06:17,933
that Felma might have
disappeared on purpose?

128
00:06:18,067 --> 00:06:20,067
Because she wanted
to get away from you?

129
00:06:21,367 --> 00:06:23,233
Manuel, please listen to me.

130
00:06:23,367 --> 00:06:25,467
I saw the neighbor has CCTV.

131
00:06:25,600 --> 00:06:27,733
Why don't we check that first?

132
00:06:27,867 --> 00:06:29,600
Don't accuse Hazel yet.

133
00:06:45,833 --> 00:06:47,167
This is from this morning.

134
00:06:49,367 --> 00:06:50,733
Thank you, sir.

135
00:06:50,867 --> 00:06:52,633
- Alright.
- Thank you, sir.

136
00:06:54,400 --> 00:06:55,733
So, Manuel.

137
00:06:55,867 --> 00:06:57,600
Do you believe me now?

138
00:07:00,400 --> 00:07:02,633
Why are you looking at me
like that?

139
00:07:03,600 --> 00:07:07,500
Can you blame me? After
everything you did to my family?

140
00:07:07,633 --> 00:07:11,833
I did all that to protect
my family, Manuel.

141
00:07:11,967 --> 00:07:15,500
That's what you never see.

142
00:07:15,667 --> 00:07:18,567
But you see Felma's pain.
You see all her suffering.

143
00:07:18,700 --> 00:07:20,733
How about my sacrifices?

144
00:07:20,867 --> 00:07:22,800
I was hospitalized.
I almost went to jail.

145
00:07:22,933 --> 00:07:24,633
You didn't care.

146
00:07:24,767 --> 00:07:26,900
Because all you
see is Felma.

147
00:07:39,467 --> 00:07:40,800
Let's go, bro.

148
00:07:47,800 --> 00:07:49,433
Wait. Bro.

149
00:07:50,333 --> 00:07:51,333
Bro.

150
00:07:52,267 --> 00:07:54,033
- Bro, wait.
- Why?

151
00:07:55,400 --> 00:07:57,900
I can't move my leg.

152
00:07:58,033 --> 00:07:59,967
- What hurts? This?
- Yeah.

153
00:08:00,100 --> 00:08:02,533
No, no. Just relax.

154
00:08:02,667 --> 00:08:04,133
Relax.

155
00:08:04,267 --> 00:08:05,833
Just relax, bro.

156
00:08:09,200 --> 00:08:10,867
Here. Maybe you've seen her.

157
00:08:11,900 --> 00:08:14,700
Okay. I'll tell Jeff.

158
00:08:14,833 --> 00:08:16,067
Jeff!

159
00:08:17,333 --> 00:08:18,233
Just a moment, please.

160
00:08:21,733 --> 00:08:23,700
Sir, this is her.

161
00:08:23,833 --> 00:08:28,167
We last saw her leaving the
airport around 11:00 A.M., sir.

162
00:08:28,300 --> 00:08:30,800
Please help us.

163
00:08:30,933 --> 00:08:33,733
That's my mom
in the photo.

164
00:08:33,867 --> 00:08:35,933
We're really
looking for her.

165
00:08:41,333 --> 00:08:42,367
What's wrong?

166
00:08:45,500 --> 00:08:48,367
Art, I need a favor.

167
00:08:48,500 --> 00:08:51,533
Can you share Felma's photo with
your friends in the press?

168
00:08:53,733 --> 00:08:55,400
We need to find her ASAP.

169
00:08:59,200 --> 00:09:00,833
What's going on?

170
00:09:00,967 --> 00:09:03,900
Why haven't they found
Ma'am Felma yet?

171
00:09:06,133 --> 00:09:07,733
- Ouch.
- Go on, bro.

172
00:09:07,867 --> 00:09:10,400
Sir Manuel?

173
00:09:10,533 --> 00:09:12,933
Dad? Dad, what happened?

174
00:09:14,967 --> 00:09:16,133
I think he got injured.

175
00:09:16,267 --> 00:09:19,167
His leg hurts. He can't move it.

176
00:09:19,300 --> 00:09:20,433
Sit down for now, bro.

177
00:09:20,567 --> 00:09:21,567
Oh no, sir.

178
00:09:21,700 --> 00:09:23,267
What do we do?

179
00:09:23,400 --> 00:09:25,567
Just straighten it.

180
00:09:25,700 --> 00:09:27,300
Dad, let's take you
to the hospital.

181
00:09:27,433 --> 00:09:29,167
No, no, no. Don't.

182
00:09:29,333 --> 00:09:31,333
Didang, get me
some medicine.

183
00:09:31,467 --> 00:09:33,833
Anything for the pain.
Any painkiller.

184
00:09:33,967 --> 00:09:35,700
Okay, sir.

185
00:09:40,067 --> 00:09:41,033
- Dad?
- Dad!

186
00:09:42,333 --> 00:09:45,833
Dad! Is there any update
about your mom?

187
00:09:47,167 --> 00:09:48,433
There's still none.

188
00:09:49,800 --> 00:09:52,200
Do you think that Hazel really
has something to do

189
00:09:52,333 --> 00:09:53,600
with Mom disappearing?

190
00:09:54,933 --> 00:09:56,633
Maybe...

191
00:09:56,767 --> 00:09:58,700
she took Mom somewhere far.

192
00:09:58,833 --> 00:10:00,367
Hid her.

193
00:10:00,500 --> 00:10:02,100
It's possible.

194
00:10:02,267 --> 00:10:04,033
But think about it.

195
00:10:04,167 --> 00:10:05,767
She didn't even know
Mom was in Davao.

196
00:10:05,900 --> 00:10:08,767
That's why she rushed
here the other day.

197
00:10:08,900 --> 00:10:11,567
It's impossible she knew
they'd be flying home today.

198
00:10:12,900 --> 00:10:14,933
Why are you defending
that woman?

199
00:10:15,067 --> 00:10:17,967
Sis, I'm not defending her.

200
00:10:18,100 --> 00:10:19,800
Can you stop fighting?

201
00:10:19,933 --> 00:10:22,133
No, Dad. It's Coleen's fault.

202
00:10:22,267 --> 00:10:23,867
You're really
pushing it with me.

203
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:25,600
Did it ever occur to you

204
00:10:25,733 --> 00:10:29,033
that Hazel might've found out
Mom was coming home today?

205
00:10:29,167 --> 00:10:30,867
That woman has
connections everywhere.

206
00:10:33,033 --> 00:10:37,133
If you hadn't messed with
the TRO, we'd be fine!

207
00:10:37,300 --> 00:10:38,800
You had it lifted!

208
00:10:46,567 --> 00:10:48,633
Damn that Manuel.

209
00:10:48,767 --> 00:10:51,667
I thought he came
here to make peace.

210
00:10:51,800 --> 00:10:54,300
Especially after the
deal I made with Coleen.

211
00:10:54,433 --> 00:10:56,200
Turns out he just
came to accuse me.

212
00:10:57,133 --> 00:10:59,100
Hey, friend, look at this.

213
00:11:03,533 --> 00:11:06,100
So she disappeared
at the airport.

214
00:11:06,233 --> 00:11:07,533
From Davao?

215
00:11:09,767 --> 00:11:13,433
The question is, why did
she suddenly disappear?

216
00:11:14,967 --> 00:11:17,067
I don't care.

217
00:11:17,200 --> 00:11:21,567
All I wish
is that they never find her.

218
00:11:29,833 --> 00:11:32,033
The news about
Felma is out.

219
00:11:33,467 --> 00:11:36,933
The police are already
tracing CCTV around the airport.

220
00:11:39,067 --> 00:11:41,167
We can't just sit here.

221
00:11:41,300 --> 00:11:43,033
- Dad. Dad.
- Dad.

222
00:11:43,200 --> 00:11:46,133
Dad.

223
00:11:46,267 --> 00:11:48,300
Dad, we'll look
for Mom ourselves.

224
00:11:48,433 --> 00:11:49,900
You stay here. Rest.

225
00:11:50,033 --> 00:11:51,767
Dear, I can't.

226
00:11:52,700 --> 00:11:54,300
Bro, listen first.

227
00:11:54,433 --> 00:11:55,800
You can't do that with
your condition right now.

228
00:11:55,933 --> 00:11:57,167
You'll just suffer.

229
00:11:57,300 --> 00:11:59,433
Stay here. Just relax.

230
00:11:59,567 --> 00:12:01,967
Let them look for her.
Let us look for her.

231
00:12:02,100 --> 00:12:05,267
Why did Mom leave
without telling anyone?

232
00:12:06,567 --> 00:12:08,800
Yeah. And if Hazel really had
nothing to do with it,

233
00:12:08,933 --> 00:12:11,000
why did Mom leave
without us knowing?

234
00:12:15,933 --> 00:12:17,933
Wait a second.

235
00:12:18,067 --> 00:12:22,700
You're hiding something
from us, aren't you?

236
00:12:22,833 --> 00:12:25,200
What happened to
Felma in Davao?

237
00:12:32,500 --> 00:12:33,867
Sir Noah.

238
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:36,200
Why won't you tell them?

239
00:12:37,567 --> 00:12:39,633
Didang, do you
know anything?

240
00:12:39,767 --> 00:12:41,467
I'm sorry.

241
00:12:41,600 --> 00:12:44,067
But Ma'am Felma told me...

242
00:12:44,200 --> 00:12:46,733
not to tell you.

243
00:12:50,100 --> 00:12:52,267
I think it's time
we tell them.

244
00:12:56,133 --> 00:12:59,067
What happened to Mom?

245
00:12:59,200 --> 00:13:00,600
Your mom is sick.

246
00:13:05,567 --> 00:13:07,800
She has a brain tumor.

247
00:13:28,800 --> 00:13:31,200
Your mom really planned
to tell you.

248
00:13:32,500 --> 00:13:37,033
But you should've told us
right away when you found out.

249
00:13:38,633 --> 00:13:40,167
Yeah, Dad.

250
00:13:40,300 --> 00:13:44,600
So we could've helped
take care of her.

251
00:13:44,733 --> 00:13:46,267
Don't blame your dad.

252
00:13:48,667 --> 00:13:51,067
He didn't know at first either.

253
00:13:51,200 --> 00:13:53,700
Your mom didn't want
you to know.

254
00:13:56,633 --> 00:13:59,167
She didn't want to add
to your worries.

255
00:14:01,267 --> 00:14:04,300
Even though she's sick,
she's still thinking about us.

256
00:14:05,700 --> 00:14:08,967
So that's why she's been acting
differently these past few days.

257
00:14:09,100 --> 00:14:11,033
The doctor warned us.

258
00:14:11,167 --> 00:14:13,367
There would be
behavioral changes.

259
00:14:15,500 --> 00:14:16,767
Memory loss.

260
00:14:18,100 --> 00:14:20,067
That might be why

261
00:14:20,200 --> 00:14:24,600
she left the airport
without telling anyone.

262
00:14:25,900 --> 00:14:27,567
That's what we think, too.

263
00:14:27,700 --> 00:14:29,367
What if...

264
00:14:29,533 --> 00:14:33,533
Hazel found out
about Mom's condition

265
00:14:33,667 --> 00:14:36,167
and took advantage of it?

266
00:14:36,300 --> 00:14:37,533
No.

267
00:14:38,867 --> 00:14:42,033
Only your dad and I
knew your mom was sick.

268
00:14:42,167 --> 00:14:43,767
We're wasting time.

269
00:14:43,900 --> 00:14:46,700
Let's go find Mom. Come on.

270
00:14:46,833 --> 00:14:48,133
Jeff.

271
00:14:50,667 --> 00:14:52,200
Jeff.

272
00:14:52,333 --> 00:14:55,100
Dad, I'll go with them.

273
00:15:11,167 --> 00:15:12,867
Bro, let's ask them.

274
00:15:13,900 --> 00:15:15,067
Miss!

275
00:15:16,267 --> 00:15:19,133
Excuse me. Have you seen her?

276
00:15:19,267 --> 00:15:20,767
- No.
- She's our mom.

277
00:15:20,900 --> 00:15:24,633
About this tall,
with long hair.

278
00:15:24,767 --> 00:15:27,133
- I'm sorry, no.
- You didn't see her?

279
00:15:27,267 --> 00:15:30,267
- No, we didn't.
- We really didn't. Sorry.

280
00:15:30,400 --> 00:15:32,467
- Okay.
- Thank you.

281
00:15:32,600 --> 00:15:33,733
I'm sorry.

282
00:15:33,867 --> 00:15:35,100
Thanks.

283
00:15:39,500 --> 00:15:43,333
Jeff, where is Mom?

284
00:15:50,533 --> 00:15:52,267
Where's Mom?

285
00:15:57,100 --> 00:15:57,967
Excuse me.

286
00:15:58,100 --> 00:16:00,933
- Do you recognize her?
- No.

287
00:16:01,067 --> 00:16:03,467
You didn't see her
walking around?

288
00:16:03,600 --> 00:16:05,833
- Are you sure?
- Yes, we're sure.

289
00:16:05,967 --> 00:16:07,567
Alright. Thank you.

290
00:16:10,133 --> 00:16:12,267
- Any lead, Joel?
- Nothing.

291
00:16:13,133 --> 00:16:14,733
Same here.

292
00:16:16,733 --> 00:16:18,200
Where could Mom be?

293
00:16:18,333 --> 00:16:19,867
Andrea, don't lose hope.

294
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:23,333
The police haven't stopped
searching. We will find her.

295
00:16:32,867 --> 00:16:34,267
Where are you, Felma?

296
00:16:36,200 --> 00:16:38,233
I'm so worried about you.

297
00:16:41,200 --> 00:16:43,267
I'm the one waiting
for you now.

298
00:16:58,533 --> 00:17:00,233
What's this?
Who's here so early?

299
00:17:02,133 --> 00:17:04,467
Who is it?

300
00:17:04,600 --> 00:17:05,600
Hey!

301
00:17:07,500 --> 00:17:10,467
Hold on! That's enough!

302
00:17:10,600 --> 00:17:13,000
Just a second!

303
00:17:13,133 --> 00:17:14,433
I'm coming!

304
00:17:31,400 --> 00:17:33,100
What are you doing here?

305
00:17:35,800 --> 00:17:37,133
I don't know.

306
00:17:38,933 --> 00:17:40,667
Felma, what's your game?

307
00:17:42,133 --> 00:17:43,833
Why are you here?

308
00:17:45,200 --> 00:17:46,933
Are you setting me up?

309
00:17:47,900 --> 00:17:49,433
So they'll think
I kidnapped you?

310
00:17:49,600 --> 00:17:51,333
So Manuel will hate me
even more?

311
00:17:52,667 --> 00:17:54,067
Manuel?

312
00:17:55,867 --> 00:17:57,200
He's here?

313
00:17:59,900 --> 00:18:02,900
Felma, stop acting.

314
00:18:03,033 --> 00:18:05,667
You can't fool me. Leave.
Go home.

315
00:18:09,033 --> 00:18:10,300
Go!

316
00:18:11,533 --> 00:18:13,633
I don't know
how to get home.

317
00:18:15,533 --> 00:18:16,867
My kids...

318
00:18:17,000 --> 00:18:19,367
Do you know where they are?

319
00:18:25,433 --> 00:18:27,400
Friend, you should call
Manuel already.

320
00:18:27,533 --> 00:18:30,000
They might accuse you
of kidnapping.

321
00:18:30,133 --> 00:18:31,700
Are they crazy?

322
00:18:31,833 --> 00:18:34,567
Felma came here
on her own.

323
00:18:34,700 --> 00:18:35,833
That's insane.

324
00:18:35,967 --> 00:18:38,267
Why would she even think
of coming to you?

325
00:18:38,400 --> 00:18:39,933
I don't know.

326
00:18:40,067 --> 00:18:42,133
But she didn't seem
like herself.

327
00:18:42,267 --> 00:18:44,267
She didn't even
recognize me.

328
00:18:44,400 --> 00:18:45,167
Oh no.

329
00:18:45,300 --> 00:18:46,700
Maybe she finally snapped

330
00:18:46,833 --> 00:18:49,000
after everything you did
to her family.

331
00:18:49,133 --> 00:18:50,767
Friend, just return her.

332
00:19:01,133 --> 00:19:02,667
- Manuel, come on!
- Felma!

333
00:19:02,800 --> 00:19:05,467
I already told you
she's not here!

334
00:19:05,600 --> 00:19:06,967
- Where is Felma?
- She's not here!

335
00:19:07,100 --> 00:19:08,233
What are you
talking about?

336
00:19:08,367 --> 00:19:10,267
<i>Friend, don't tell me you've
gone as far as kidnapping.</i>

337
00:19:10,400 --> 00:19:11,533
<i> What are you saying?</i>

338
00:19:11,667 --> 00:19:13,367
<i>- Nothing!
- You're lying!</i>

339
00:19:13,500 --> 00:19:15,433
<i> Where is Felma?</i>

340
00:19:15,567 --> 00:19:16,733
<i> Where is she?</i>

341
00:19:16,867 --> 00:19:18,633
<i> Let go. Let go of me!</i>

342
00:19:30,667 --> 00:19:32,733
Here. Drink this first.

343
00:19:37,667 --> 00:19:39,700
Where did you come from?

344
00:19:39,833 --> 00:19:42,400
Why do you look
so exhausted?

345
00:20:04,400 --> 00:20:07,433
Someone said
they saw Mom in Baclaran.

346
00:20:07,567 --> 00:20:11,000
She was walking alone,
looking for a ride.

347
00:20:11,133 --> 00:20:13,233
A ride to where?

348
00:20:13,367 --> 00:20:15,400
That's the thing, Dad.

349
00:20:15,533 --> 00:20:18,000
Mom couldn't say.

350
00:20:18,133 --> 00:20:21,933
That's why the person
got confused, too.

351
00:20:22,067 --> 00:20:23,233
It looks like Mom forgot.

352
00:20:23,367 --> 00:20:25,433
Thank you so much.

353
00:20:25,567 --> 00:20:27,000
Thank you. Alright.
We're heading there now.

354
00:20:28,767 --> 00:20:30,133
I've got a lead.

355
00:20:31,500 --> 00:20:33,267
I know where your mom is.

356
00:20:40,333 --> 00:20:42,133
My head hurts.

357
00:20:43,533 --> 00:20:45,767
Can you bring me home?

358
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:51,567
Okay, I'll call
you a taxi.

359
00:20:53,833 --> 00:20:55,700
Finish your water first.

360
00:21:52,267 --> 00:21:54,867
This is from
the Manila Traffic Authority.

361
00:21:55,000 --> 00:21:56,567
Arjun sent it to me.

362
00:21:57,600 --> 00:21:58,867
Uncle, let me pause it.

363
00:22:00,200 --> 00:22:02,233
Then let's zoom in
on the plate number.

364
00:22:03,567 --> 00:22:04,567
There, Dad.

365
00:22:07,233 --> 00:22:08,867
Let's call Colonel Sarabia.

366
00:22:09,000 --> 00:22:10,667
Alright, Dad. I'll do it.

367
00:22:51,833 --> 00:22:53,033
Hazel, come on!

368
00:22:53,167 --> 00:22:55,300
I don't trust
that laugh of yours.

369
00:22:55,433 --> 00:22:57,067
Are you planning
something again?

370
00:22:57,200 --> 00:22:59,700
What if I help her?

371
00:22:59,833 --> 00:23:01,067
Just pretend.

372
00:23:01,200 --> 00:23:03,700
We're probably close friends.

373
00:23:03,833 --> 00:23:07,333
We can call each other "friend."

374
00:23:07,467 --> 00:23:10,667
Friend, I forgot
to take my medicine.

375
00:23:13,400 --> 00:23:15,733
I'll take her to the hospital.

376
00:23:15,867 --> 00:23:17,133
But let her suffer
a little first.

377
00:23:17,267 --> 00:23:20,233
Miss Felma, you have visitors.

378
00:23:21,633 --> 00:23:23,933
Doctor, who brought her here?

379
00:23:24,100 --> 00:23:25,733
We just want to thank them.

380
00:23:25,867 --> 00:23:27,200
Me.

381
00:23:28,533 --> 00:23:29,700
So Mom was with you all along.

382
00:23:29,833 --> 00:23:31,567
Why did you kidnap her?

383
00:23:32,933 --> 00:23:36,267
Why are you picking a fight
with my best friend?
